Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.75,0:00:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This fixture begins with a clear voice and enough silence for the detector to settle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.65,0:00:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each caption line uses ordinary words so subtitle synchronization can focus on timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.09,0:00:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third sentence is intentionally longer and gives the alignment code a wider speech island.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.18,0:00:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After a pause the speaker continues with another compact sentence for the next cue.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.58,0:00:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A reliable fixture needs variation in length without becoming a long audiobook.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.19,0:00:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This cue mentions video containers audio codecs and subtitle rewrites in plain language.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.79,0:00:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next phrase arrives after silence so the voice activity detector can split the span.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.64,0:00:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Short captions still matter because real subtitle files often mix brief and longer lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.92,0:01:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another sentence adds more timing evidence before the final codec cases begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.48,0:01:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Near the end we keep the same calm delivery and leave room for timing drift checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.89,0:01:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One more cue gives the stretch test a broader timeline across the fixture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.06,0:01:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final spoken cue closes the fixture with a simple sentence and a clean ending.
